Package com.im.njams.sdk

Class Njams

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.im.njams.sdk.Njams
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InstructionListener
    public class Njams
extends Object
implements InstructionListener
    This is an instance of nJAMS. It cares about lifecycle and initializations and holds references to the process models and global variables.
    Author:
    bwand

        public <T> Serializer<T> addSerializer​(Class<T> key,
                                       Serializer<? super T> serializer)
        Adds a Serializer for serializing a given class.
        Uses serialize(java.lang.Object) to serialize instances of this class with the registered serializer. If a serializer is already registered, it will be replaced with the new serializer.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type that the given instance serializes
        Parameters:
        key - Class for which the serializer should be registered
        serializer - A serializer that can serialize instances of class key to strings.
        Returns:
        If a serializer for the same type was already registered before, the former registered serializer is returned. Otherwise null is returned.

      • findSerializer

        public <T> Serializer<? super T> findSerializer​(Class<T> clazz)
        Gets the serializer with the given class key. If no serializer is registered yet, the superclass hierarchy will be checked recursively. If neither the class nor any superclass is registered, the interface hierarchy will be checked recursively. if no (super) interface is registered, null will be returned.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type of the class
        Parameters:
        clazz - Class for which a serializer will be searched.
        Returns:
        Serializer or null.
